started, back to microfinance.

00:23:58.280 --> 00:24:00.807
I want to talk about banking
and microfinance now.

00:24:00.807 --> 00:24:02.890
What's interesting is that
here in Silicon Valley,

00:24:02.890 --> 00:24:05.990
there's been a number
of startups who said,

00:24:05.990 --> 00:24:08.710
many people cannot get loans
because they don't have

00:24:08.710 --> 00:24:09.700
traditional credit.

00:24:09.700 --> 00:24:12.035
We have a credit system in
the US, have a credit score.

00:24:12.035 --> 00:24:13.410
One of three big
credit agencies,

00:24:13.410 --> 00:24:16.330
and if you're not on there and
you don't have a great credit

00:24:16.330 --> 00:24:17.780
score, you can't get a loan.

00:24:17.780 --> 00:24:20.470
And so these startups said,
we have a brand new idea.

00:24:20.470 --> 00:24:22.930
Our idea is we're going to
use your social reputation.

00:24:22.930 --> 00:24:24.190
We're going to check
out social media.

00:24:24.190 --> 00:24:25.390
We're going to use
other things like that.

00:24:25.390 --> 00:24:27.730
And of course, that's not
a very new idea at all

00:24:27.730 --> 00:24:31.120
because you started
that 30 plus years ago.

00:24:31.120 --> 00:24:32.914
But they actually
have been successful.

00:24:32.914 --> 00:24:34.330
And their repayment
rates are very

00:24:34.330 --> 00:24:37.420
high because they are using
these alternative ways

00:24:37.420 --> 00:24:38.690
[INAUDIBLE].

00:24:38.690 --> 00:24:41.110
But in terms of the large
banking infrastructure,

00:24:41.110 --> 00:24:42.610
the large banks
of the world, what

00:24:42.610 --> 00:24:44.770
has been their current
stance towards microfinance?

00:24:44.770 --> 00:24:45.760
You've proved it.

00:24:45.760 --> 00:24:47.735
Grameen America now has
proved it right here

00:24:47.735 --> 00:24:48.610
in the United States.

00:24:48.610 --> 00:24:50.230
This is not something
that just works overseas.

00:24:50.230 --> 00:24:52.480
It works right here at
scale, a billion dollars

00:24:52.480 --> 00:24:55.450
of loans going out next year.

00:24:55.450 --> 00:24:58.840
I know Deutsche Bank had a
microfinance-oriented support

00:24:58.840 --> 00:24:59.956
for some time.

00:24:59.956 --> 00:25:01.080
What has been the reaction?

00:25:01.080 --> 00:25:03.607
And what would you want
to see the large banks do?

00:25:03.607 --> 00:25:05.190
MUHAMMAD YUNUS: This
is a battle which

00:25:05.190 --> 00:25:07.620
was going on for many,
many years with me,

00:25:07.620 --> 00:25:10.030
challenging them why
you should do that.

00:25:10.030 --> 00:25:14.050
Now I keep saying that yes, it's
very difficult for these banks

00:25:14.050 --> 00:25:16.360
to come to the poor
people because it's

00:25:16.360 --> 00:25:18.150
designed for the rich.

00:25:18.150 --> 00:25:20.890
I said, the structure and the
architecture of the banking

00:25:20.890 --> 00:25:24.350
system is it's designed
on the more you have,

00:25:24.350 --> 00:25:25.780
the more you get.

00:25:25.780 --> 00:25:27.590
So it doesn't translate itself.

00:25:27.590 --> 00:25:29.590
If you have less, you
don't get anything.

00:25:29.590 --> 00:25:31.850
You have none, you get nothing.

00:25:31.850 --> 00:25:34.630
So we need a different
kind of architecture

00:25:34.630 --> 00:25:36.290
to create bank for the poor.

00:25:36.290 --> 00:25:37.450
So one is a bank for rich.

00:25:37.450 --> 00:25:38.920
Another is bank for the poor.

00:25:38.920 --> 00:25:41.140
That's architecture that
we used in Bangladesh,

00:25:41.140 --> 00:25:43.930
created different
legislation for ourselves

00:25:43.930 --> 00:25:45.420
to create the bank for the poor.

00:25:45.420 --> 00:25:48.370
The bank for the poor has
not been created elsewhere.

00:25:48.370 --> 00:25:51.820
We have been encouraging
India for many years

00:25:51.820 --> 00:25:52.810
to create that law.

00:25:52.810 --> 00:25:54.780
But that [? dog ?] got
[? clocked ?] in the parliament

00:25:54.780 --> 00:25:56.530
with the select
committee, this committee.

00:25:56.530 --> 00:25:59.320
It doesn't come out
of the legislation.

00:25:59.320 --> 00:26:01.930
So we are encouraging
Indian authorities

00:26:01.930 --> 00:26:05.920
to make big NGOs, who
became very successful, very

00:26:05.920 --> 00:26:07.190
good microfinance program.

00:26:07.190 --> 00:26:09.610
But NGO, they always
depend on outside money.

00:26:09.610 --> 00:26:13.060
So I have requested the central
bank, Reserve Bank of India,

00:26:13.060 --> 00:26:16.420
to give them a temporary
limited license that they

00:26:16.420 --> 00:26:18.740
can do what they are doing,
nothing more than that.

00:26:18.740 --> 00:26:21.040
But they will be allowed
to take deposits.

00:26:21.040 --> 00:26:23.500
So now there are 10 licenses
that have been issued.

00:26:23.500 --> 00:26:25.420
So now they are very happy
because they have disconnected

00:26:25.420 --> 00:26:26.474
with the international--

00:26:26.474 --> 00:26:28.140
JACK HIDARY: And
deposits are coming in.

00:26:28.140 --> 00:26:29.931
MUHAMMAD YUNUS: And
deposits are coming in.

00:26:29.931 --> 00:26:31.070
So that's another thing.

00:26:31.070 --> 00:26:33.790
So we need to create a
different sorts of [INAUDIBLE]..

00:26:33.790 --> 00:26:36.950
I give the example of
the conventional banks

00:26:36.950 --> 00:26:39.040
are like a supertanker.

00:26:39.040 --> 00:26:42.640
They go into deep sea, carry
lots of weight and materials

00:26:42.640 --> 00:26:43.463
with them.

00:26:43.463 --> 00:26:47.730
I said, but the microcredit
is a dinghy boat.

00:26:47.730 --> 00:26:49.600
It doesn't need a deep sea.

00:26:49.600 --> 00:26:52.990
It goes from little
shallow water and so on.

00:26:52.990 --> 00:26:55.480
The architecture
of a supertanker,

00:26:55.480 --> 00:26:58.672
you cannot design a dinghy
boat with architecture

00:26:58.672 --> 00:26:59.380
of a supertanker.

00:26:59.380 --> 00:27:02.425
Then it'll drown itself.

00:27:02.425 --> 00:27:04.550
So I said, why don't you
design a new architecture?

00:27:04.550 --> 00:27:06.520
There's a new
legislative formula.

00:27:06.520 --> 00:27:08.290
If you have the
resource, everybody

00:27:08.290 --> 00:27:11.980
